headline: Figma sheds $11 billion in market value days after blockbuster IPO
summary: NEW YORK (Reuters) -Shares of Figma slumped 23% on profit taking on Monday, as euphoria over the design software firm waned days after its blockbuster initial public offering.  San Francisco, California-based Figma shares had scored a massive 250% gain during their market debut on Thursday when they were priced at $33 but finished at $115.50, giving the company a market capitalization of about $56.3 billion.  Figma's market value closed at $59.5 billion on Friday after its shares rose 5.6% to $122.

headline: Lyft, China's Baidu to launch robotaxi service in Europe next year
summary: (Reuters) -U.S. ride-hailing company Lyft said on Monday it will partner with China's Baidu to deploy robotaxis across Europe starting next year, marking the Chinese search engine giant's first foray into the European self-driven taxi sector.  The partnership will launch initially in Germany and the United Kingdom, with Baidu’s electric RT6 robotaxis operating on Lyft’s platform pending regulatory approval.  The rollout aims to scale to thousands of vehicles across Europe in the coming years, leveraging Lyft’s $200 million acquisition of European mobility app FreeNow, completed on Thursday.
